WendyTravel2012
3632
Reviewed October 22, 2019
Good food and service
It's a recommended place and one of the top ten places to eat in Danang according to the internet so we went there to eat.
In addition to BBQ raw items their menu also lists cooked dishes like porridge, steamed squids, etc. We ordered fish with banana in spicy sauce and it came with white noodles. Nice and spicy. The BBQ items were well marinated, some with lemongrass and they cook quickly on the grill. Nice sauces to dip them in. Free mustard greens to wrap your food too.
They have the usual height tables and chairs as well as the low tables with stools. We took the latter. It was a different experience grilling and eating closer to the ground.
Service is prompt and they even change the grill midway so we had a clean grill to continue cooking.
Be aware that your clothes will smell of the BBQ aroma after the dinner.
I would recommend this place too.
See all 6 reviews by WendyTravel2012 for Da Nang
