thechronictraveller
Phoenix, Arizona
218160
Reviewed September 20, 2019
Good self-cook BBQ in a local atmosphere
When you want a nice cold beer and grilled meat, this is the place to go. The setting is casual, noisy and chaotic, and if you sit inside it can get quite smoky. Waiters run around delivering buckets of hot coals and raw meat to tables in an expert fashion. When it's crowded service can be a bit slow, but sit back an enjoy a cold Larue beer and some complimentary quail eggs. Lots of different seasoned meats and seafood to choose from, and you cook at the table-top grill. Great value for the money.
Date of visit: October 2018
Ask thechronictraveller about Quan Com Hue Ngon
